Minnesota Territory (1849-03-03)

1849/03/03 -> 1858/05/10

The United States created Minnesota Territory from unorganized federal territory west of the Mississippi River (formerly part of Iowa Territory) and de facto Wisconsin Territory.

(U.S. Stat., vol. 9, ch. 121 [1849]/pp. 403-409)
